description.narrative:
Humanitarian Initiative Just Relief Aid (HIJRA) will work with community structures and district on community engagement and protection activities and leading risk communication interventions. HIJRA will in this project consolidate their  hygiene promotional and sanitation activities by making them COVID 19 sensitive. Together with Oxfam, HIJRA will work with COVID-19 task Force under the Risk Communication, Social Mobilization and Community Engagement Pillar to ensure hygiene promotional strategies and approached are well aligned to the current priorities and harmonized across response areas. The partner will support the Village Health Team (VHT) approach promoted by the MoH to ensure sustainability of interventions.
Specific activities will include;
 Community awareness creation and sensitization on COVID-19 and its prevention (observing physical/social distancing, good respiratory and hand hygiene etc), nonviolent conflict resolution, and available GBV services and referrals pathways. Community awareness will be through digital and other social media platforms, including two-way communication channels that goes beyond just sharing messages and into actual dialogueand engagement radio talk shows where listeners call in and ask questions to enhance community engagement). Conduct trainings on hygiene and sanitation practices, and solid waste management to market committees, RWC and market vendors in line with COVID 19 prevention and control. Production and installation of the translated COVID 19 IEC materials (posters and visibility boards) at markets, religious/ cultural gathering locations and trading centres. Support to personal health safety of VHTs and water point caretakers through provision of PPEs (re-usable facemasks and pocket size sanitizers). Skilling and equipping selected community-based groups on soap production to enhance hand washing and boost their livelihood in the post-pandemic era. (immediate soap distributions being carried out already by UNHCR and partners) Dissemination of translated hygiene and risk-awareness audio messaging on COVID-19 and countering misinformation to communities through Boda Boda Talk Talk, radio talk shows/forums – addressing also the different levels of education of communities and the different ways in which man and women access information.
